Program: The History Hour
Title: Conflict timber in Liberia's civil war
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csypz2
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 16 Sep 2019
How the timber industry fuelled a brutal civil war in West Africa, the Honduran coup that left the president holed up in an embassy plus the Indian affirmative action controversy, the first ever voyage all the way around the globe 500 years ago and the sit-com "Friends" hits TV screens worldwide. (Photo: Timber near Buchanan in Liberia in 2010. Credit: Getty Images) Show less